#Pauline Johnson (Tekahionwake)

Emily Pauline Johnson is a Indigenous poet. She was born in 1861 on the Six Nations
Reserve in Canada West. Some of her poplar poems include "The Song My Paddle Sings" and 
"A Cry from an Indian Wife".

Source: Pauline Johnson (Tekahionwake), *An Anthology of Canadian Literature in English*, 
edited by Donna Bennett and Russell Brown, Oxford University Press, 2019, 204-206.
